BAKED CUSTARD 
 
3 large (or 4 smaller) eggs 
 
1/3 cup sugar 
 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
 
Pinch of salt 
 
2 1/2 cups warm milk (120 to 130 degrees) 
 
Ground nutmeg 
 
Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla, and salt in medium bowl. Gradually add milk. Pour into custard cups or a casserole baking dish and sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in preheated 350-degree oven for about 30 minutes for custard cups or 45 minutes for baking dish. Custard is done when a knife inserted between center and edge of dish comes out clean. Cool before serving and keep leftovers in refrigerator. 
 
NOTE: I never bother to warm the milk although most recipes mention doing it. Many recipes recommend setting the cups or baking dish in a larger pan and adding hot water to the pan, up to the level of the custard, for the baking process. I tried it once and nearly scalded myself when I splashed the hot water on myself while taking the baked dish out of the oven. I am clumsy, so I don’t bake custard with a surrounding hot water bath and they come out fine and without the chance of hot water cascading over me and the kitchen floor. 
 
My “never measure” recipe is — per each cup of milk; 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 to 1capful of vanilla, pinch of salt and nutmeg sprinkled on top and baked in moderate oven. 
 
