GRANDMA NICHOLS’ STOVE-TOP RICE PUDDING 
 
1 quart milk 
 
1 teacupful (about 3/4 measuring cup) uncooked rice 
 
1 large egg 
 
1/2 cup sugar 
 
2 full capfuls (2 teaspoons) vanilla extract 
 
Pinch salt 
 
Ground nutmeg or cinnamon 
 
Warm milk, in medium size saucepan, over low to medium heat and stir in rice as soon as milk starts to warm up. Bring to a simmer and cook, uncovered and stirring frequently, until the rice is very tender, about 30 to 35 minutes. In a bowl, beat the egg and add sugar, vanilla and salt. Gradually add the cooked rice to the egg mixture until well blended, and then return all to the saucepan. Cook and stir for a minute or two to cook the egg. Pour into custard cups or serving dish and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon. Refrigerate until chilled. 
 
