TAPIOCA PUDDING 
 
1 quart milk (4 cups) 
 
1/2 cup sugar 
 
3 large eggs 
 
1/4 teaspoon salt 
 
1/4 cup Minute tapioca 
 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
 
Ground nutmeg 
 
In a heavy saucepan, beat well the eggs, sugar, and salt together. Add the milk, vanilla and tapioca granules and let set for a few minutes to let the tapioca start to soften. Over medium high heat, bring the mixture almost to a boil, stirring constantly. When the mixture starts to show a slow boil and is thickening, remove from the heat. Pour into a serving bowl to cool and sprinkle with ground nutmeg. It can also be eaten warm. 
 
