RHUBARB CUSTARD PIE 
 
3 cups cut up rhubarb 
 
1 1/2 cups sugar 
 
2 eggs, beaten 
 
2 tablespoons flour 
 
Zest of 1/2 lemon 
 
Juice of 1/2 a lemon 
 
2 unbaked crusts for 10-inch deep dish pie 
 
Mix rhubarb, sugar, eggs, flour, lemon zest and lemon juice. Fit one crust into pie pan and sprinkle bottom with a little addition flour. Fill shell with rhubarb mixture. Cut second crust into strips and make a lattice top for the pie. Brush the lattice strips with a little cream or milk or beaten egg wash and sprinkle with sugar. Bake in preheated 450-degree oven for 10 minutes, and then reduce heat to 350-degrees and bake until knife inserted in pie comes out clean, about 45 to 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Serve with a dip of good Vanilla Ice Cream. 
 
