FRESH STRAWBERRY PIE w/CREAM CHEESE 
 
1 graham cracker pie crust 
 
1 quart fresh strawberries 
 
1 (8-ounce) package cream cheese 
 
1/4 cup sugar 
 
2 teaspoons lemon juice 
 
1/2 cup heavy whipping cream 
 
1 package strawberry glaze 
 
Whipped topping (or more whipping cream, whipped and sweetened) 
 
Wash strawberries and cut into halves or smaller if the berries are large. Let the cream cheese come to room temperature. With electric mixer, beat cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice until well mixed. Add whipping cream and beat until light and fluffy. Spread in piecrust. Top with strawberries, then the glaze. Frost pie with the whipped topping (or the additional whipping cream, whipped and sweetened, if calories are not a problem). Use a large decorating star tube to add this “meringue” , if available. Keep chilled. 
 
