APPLE CAKE 
 
11/4 cups sifted flour 
 
1 teaspoon baking powder 
 
1/4 teaspoon salt 
 
1 tablespoon sugar 
 
1/2 cup butter 
 
1 egg yolk, beaten 
 
2 tablespoon milk 
 
3 cups sliced apples 
 
Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. With an electric mixer, in mixer bowl, cream butter, then add dry ingredients and mix. Combine egg yolk and milk and add to butter mixture and mix. Press this mixture on bottom of a buttered 8- x 8-inch pan. Overlap apple slices on top of this dough. 
 
Sprinkle with topping and bake in preheated 375-degree oven for about 50 minutes. 
 
TOPPING: 
 
3/4 cup sugar 
 
1 1/2 tablespoons flour 
 
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon 
 
2 tablespoons butter 
 
1/4 teaspoon lemon zest 
 
Mix sugar, flour, lemon zest and cinnamon. Cut in butter until it is like coarse cornmeal. 
 
